title: Uber to invest over $100 million in autonomous vehicle charging amid robotaxi push

The move includes building DC fast charging stations at its autonomous depots ​where Uber runs day-to-day fleet operations, and at pit stops throughout priority cities.  Uber has made autonomous vehicles a key strategic priority, partnering with more than 20 firms across the world on self-driving freight, delivery ‌and taxi services, as ⁠it races to secure market share and fight competition from companies such as Tesla.
